headline: Should Principal Financial Group’s 2025 Payouts and Higher Dividend Require Action From PFG Investors?
summary: Principal Financial Group recently reported full-year 2025 results showing revenue of US$15,625.5 million and net income of US$1,185.1 million, alongside fourth-quarter adjusted earnings per share of US$2.19 on revenue of US$4.46 billion. In tandem with these results, the company boosted its first-quarter 2026 dividend to US$0.80 per share and returned over US$1.5 billion to shareholders in 2025 through dividends and share repurchases.
